SEE 3 REASONS WHY YOU NEED TO CHOOSE THE RIGHT JUMP ROPE!⬇️
 
Safety: Choosing the right jump rope for your skill level and workout goals can help you avoid injury

Comfort: Jumping rope can be hard on your feet, ankles, and wrists, especially if you’re doing it for an extended period of time. Choosing a jump rope that’s comfortable to hold and that has the right weight and thickness for your body can help you avoid discomfort and fatigue. A well-designed jump rope will also allow you to maintain good form and reduce unnecessary strain on your body.

Performance: The right jump rope can help you perform better and achieve your fitness goals more efficiently. If you’re trying to build speed or endurance, for example, you’ll want a jump rope that’s designed for those purposes.

Ir noslēdzies astoņu dienu piedzīvojums unikālās un aizraujošās “Personības akadēmijas” nometnes dalībniekiem, ir piedzīvotas tik daudz emocijas, iegūtas nebijušas pieredzes un zināšanas, jauni draugi no visas Latvijas un neaizmirstamas atmiņas. 

Tik daudz aktivitātes, lekcijas un pieredzes stāsti tikai dažās dienās, tomēr pats gaidītākais un reizē izaicinošākais bija pārgājiens, pēc kura dalībnieki nakšņoja teltīs. Komandas sadarbības prasmes, par kurām ar jauniešiem katru dienu runāja personības attīstības treneris Guntis Jansons, tika pārbaudītas un  attīstītas laivu braucienā pa Gauju. Taču peldētprasmes tika pilnveidotas Valmieras olimpiskā centra peldbaseinā profesionāla trenera vadībā.  Sengrieķu olimpiskajās spēlēs jaunieši uzzināja par Olimpisko spēļu vēsturi un  kino vakarā ar latviešu kino mākslu - Matīsa Spailes filmu “Mūsējie”. Badijs Lī iedvesmoja jauniešus, kā realizēt savu sapni, ja nāc no ne visai turīgas sešu bērnu ģimenes, bet ir liels sapnis. Lai būtu veiksmīgi, ir svarīgi radīt labu tēlu, to jaunieši apguva “Tik-Tok” meistarklasē. Noslēgumā jaunieši atklāja savus talantus “Talantu šovā”. Nometnes laikā neskaitāmas aktivitātes attīstīja jauniešos dažādas personības šķautnes, kuras būs kā pamats personības attīstībai. Veiksmi tālākajā ceļā un tiekamies nākamgad!

2 YEARS OF JUMP ROPE PROGRESS with the @buddyleejumpropes System!🔥

🔗 The Buddy Lee Training System & Jump Rope has been a key throughout this amazing journey.

I still remember that when I met Buddy, I wanted to immediately start to do all the cool skills as I felt I’m ready because I had prior experience with jump rope from boxing.

And I felt athletic enough to start learning, but Buddy made me realize that most of the things I thought I knew about jump rope were wrong.

He told me that I should first master the basics and so that’s what I did.

In order to jump safely, have the jump rope capacity and the ability to shift from one skill to another smoothly, the basics must be mastered first.

When you master the basics first, you will slowly start to feel like one with the rope, and learning advanced skills will start to feel possible.

Consistent jumping with the rope also develops your - Discipline, Patience, Focus and Commitment.

As with everything that’s worth striving for, you will need those qualities.

Read this if you want to master the jump rope↓
-
1. Start with just the Basic Bounce: Work on keeping your back straight, arms close to the sides, move only your wrists, jump on the balls of your feet and jump just 1 to 2 inches off the ground.

2. Choose the right Rope Length: A good rope just barely touches the ground when you jump over it, start with the surface-to-shoulder measurement where you stand with 1 leg  on the middle of the rope cord, both handles should come to the shoulder evenly, cut the rest of the cord or tie knots if needed.

3. Film your progress: Preferably every training, that way you can see what needs correction and you’ll be able to fix your mistakes and make progress faster.

4. Build Stamina Slowly: Start with short sessions, they can be even 3 minutes, divided in 30 seconds of jumping & 30 seconds of resting, then make them longer over time, proper technique comes first. 

5. Stretch your major Muscle groups: Such as your calves, quadriceps, hamstrings, and shoulders. Hold each stretch for 15-30 seconds.This will help improve flexibility and reduce muscle tightness.
-
Remember that Jumping Rope is a skilled movement that requires discipline and practice to master, follow the Buddy Lee Training System and you’ll be sure to master the basics of jump rope.
